Jan 12 24
Dear Mama: 
I dreamed about you last night & awoke fearing you. Might be rich. Don't get sick, please, - not till I get home anyway. Take the best of care of yourself. What a cold time you must be having. 10 below! Good heavens! It's may here night & day - wonderful. 
I have been at Bruminstool's home most of two days meeting old Indian fighters - one of them fought on the Little Big Horn. Five old men! One was Colonel Wheeler who owned the pony Crazy Horse rode in the Custer Fight. I know just how that pony looked! 

